history.content:
Math 160, History of Mathematics, is really cool.

I only went to one class and had to drop due to time conflict, but you essentially go through historical proofs by various early mathematicians. It's a small class (but I believe there's still space).

I'm a senior EECS looking for an HSS upperdiv thats more technical in nature. Im thinking right now about Econ 101A. I feel good about the math parts but I haven't taken Econ 1/2. Will this be a problem? I'm interested in something that delves more into theory behind the math than Econ 101A, but doesn't require too much subject area knowledge. Most of all, I need it to fulfill the upper div Humanity/Social Science requirement for College of Engineering. Does anyone have any recommendations?
history.subject: Recommendations for HSS upperdiv
